<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFSchoch1994">Schoch, Russell (September 1994). "<a href="http://www.alumni.berkeley.edu/Alumni/Cal_Monthly/September_1994/QA_-_A_Conversation_with_Kerry_Mullis.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.alumni.berkeley.edu/Alumni/Cal_Monthly/September_1994/QA_-_A_Conversation_with_Kerry_Mullis.asp" rel="nofollow">Q&amp;A - A Conversation with Kerry Mullis</a>". <i>California Monthly</i> (Berkley, CA: California Alumni Association) <b>105</b> (1): 20<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.alumni.berkeley.edu/Alumni/Cal_Monthly/September_1994/QA_-_A_Conversation_with_Kerry_Mullis.asp" class="external free" title="http://www.alumni.berkeley.edu/Alumni/Cal_Monthly/September_1994/QA_-_A_Conversation_with_Kerry_Mullis.asp" rel="nofollow">http://www.alumni.berkeley.edu/Alumni/Cal_Monthly/September_1994/QA_-_A_Conversation_with_Kerry_Mullis.asp</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-11</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Q%26A+-+A+Conversation+with+Kerry+Mullis&amp;rft.jtitle=California+Monthly&amp;rft.aulast=Schoch&amp;rft.aufirst=Russell&amp;rft.au=Schoch%2C+Russell&amp;rft.date=September+1994&amp;rft.volume=105&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=20&amp;rft.place=Berkley%2C+CA&amp;rft.pub=California+Alumni+Association&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.alumni.berkeley.edu%2FAlumni%2FCal_Monthly%2FSeptember_1994%2FQA_-_A_Conversation_with_Kerry_Mullis.asp&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Kary_Mullis"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFAnn_Harrison2006">Ann Harrison (2006-01-16). <a href="http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2006/01/70015" class="external text" title="http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2006/01/70015" rel="nofollow">"LSD: The Geek's Wonder Drug?"</a>. <i>Wired</i>. Wired<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2006/01/70015" class="external free" title="http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2006/01/70015" rel="nofollow">http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2006/01/70015</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-11</span>.  "Like Herbert, many scientists and engineers also report heightened states of creativity while using LSD. During a press conference on Friday, Hofmann revealed that he was told by Nobel-prize-winning chemist Kary Mullis that LSD had helped him develop the polymerase chain reaction that helps amplify specific DNA sequences."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=LSD%3A+The+Geek%27s+Wonder+Drug%3F&amp;rft.atitle=Wired&amp;rft.aulast=Ann+Harrison&amp;rft.au=Ann+Harrison&amp;rft.date=2006-01-16&amp;rft.pub=Wired&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fscience%2Fdiscoveries%2Fnews%2F2006%2F01%2F70015&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Kary_Mullis"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
